HEADWORD: Stag-horned
<hw>Stag"-horned`</hw> <pr>(-h⟦ocir⟧rnd`)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Having the mandibles large and palmate, or
branched somewhat like the antlers of a stag; -- said of certain
beetles.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

